cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.SDSP, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper proposes a new binaural beamforming technique for noise reduction and binaural cue preservation in audio signals. 
- cs.SI (Speech and Natural Language Processing): The proposed method can be applied to speech signals to improve speech intelligibility in noisy environments. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a method for controlling the trade-off between noise reduction and binaural cue preservation, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.SDSP (Signal Processing): The paper proposes a signal processing technique for binaural beamforming. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The proposed method can be applied to improve the quality of audio signals in multimedia applications.
